= xdebug_get_declared_vars
Returns declared variables
array
none
FUNC_STACK_TRACE

TXT:
Returns an array where each element is a variable name which is defined and
<b>used</b> in the current scope:
EXAMPLE: 
<?php
    class strings {
        static function fix_strings($a, $b) {
            foreach ($b as $item) {
            }
            var_dump(xdebug_get_declared_vars());
        }
    }
    strings::fix_strings(array(1,2,3), array(4,5,6));
?>
RESULT:
array(2) {
  [0]=&gt;
  string(1) "b"
  [1]=&gt;
  string(4) "item"
}
TXT:
The variable name "a" is not returned here, as it is not used in that scope.
